Installing OCEMR for Development or Testing
===========================================

Preparing the Environment
-------------------------

 -  Install Prerequisites:

    $ sudo apt-get install python-django python-sqlite

 -  Git a copy of the software:

    $ git clone git://github.com/ph1l/ocemr.git

 -  Checkout the development branch:

    $ git checkout develop

 -  Copy the config File:

    $ cp settings.py.DIST settings.py

 -  Edit the config file:

    $ vi settings.py

     -  For testing leave the DATABASE_ENGINE set to sqlite3
     -  change DATABASE_NAME to reflect a different location if you wish
     -  change APP_PATH and TIME_ZONE 

 -  Setup version.py:

    $ ./util/make_version.sh  > version.py

 -  Setup Utilities Configuration:

    $ cp ./util/util_conf.py.DIST ./util/util_conf.py
    $ vi ./util/util_conf.py

     -  Edit the APP_PATH

